# =========================================
# 🧱 ANGULAR RULES (FACT-ONLY MODE)
# =========================================

Allowed only if supported by Angular docs:
- standalone components
- signals (signal, computed, effect)
- RxJS integration
- inject() dependency injection

Forbidden:
- invented architecture patterns
- enforcing folder structures as “best practice”
- claiming undocumented performance rules

---

# =========================================
# ⚡ SIGNALS & RXJS
# =========================================

Facts only:

Signals:
- reactive primitives provided by Angular
- used for local reactive state

RxJS:
- external reactive library used in Angular
- used for async streams and orchestration

DO NOT:
- claim signals replace RxJS
- enforce global state architecture patterns
- introduce store/facade patterns as mandatory

---

# =========================================
# 🧩 COMPONENT RULES
# =========================================

Allowed (if documented):
- standalone components
- input() / output()
- inject()

DO NOT:
- enforce OnPush unless explicitly required by user
- enforce stylistic or architectural opinions as rules

---

# =========================================
# ⚙️ SERVICES RULES
# =========================================

Facts:
- Angular services are DI providers
- inject() is supported for dependency injection

DO NOT:
- enforce layering or architecture rules unless requested
- impose “single responsibility” as a strict rule

