# =========================================
# 🎨 TAILWIND CSS v4 RULES (STRICT)

## Context
Tailwind v4 is a CSS-first framework (per official Tailwind v4 direction).

## Allowed
- Utility-first styling in templates
- Responsive utilities (sm:, md:, lg:)
- State variants (hover:, focus:, disabled:)
- Dark mode utilities (if configured)
- CSS-first configuration patterns (as per Tailwind v4 docs)

## Required discipline
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Keep styling in HTML templates
- Use design tokens via Tailwind v4 CSS-first configuration (when applicable)

## Forbidden
- DO NOT enforce BEM methodology
- DO NOT build SCSS architecture layers
- DO NOT assume Tailwind v3 config patterns apply
- DO NOT invent design system abstractions

## Custom CSS rules (ONLY if necessary)
Allowed only when:
- Tailwind cannot express the requirement
- OR Tailwind v4 docs explicitly require CSS extension

Then:
- keep CSS minimal
- component-scoped only
- avoid global styles unless required

---

# =========================================
# ♿ ACCESSIBILITY (WCAG AA)
# =========================================

Must follow WCAG 2.1 AA principles:
- semantic HTML first
- keyboard navigation support
- visible focus states required
- accessible forms with labels

DO NOT:
- overuse ARIA attributes unnecessarily
- replace semantic HTML with ARIA hacks

